# Next.js (App Router) conventions

- **Server Components by default.** Only add `'use client'` for state/effects/browser APIs;
  push client boundaries to the leaves.
- Fetch data in Server Components or server actions — not in `useEffect`.
- `async`/`await` Server Components are fine; don't make a component client just to fetch.
- Be explicit about caching: set `cache`/`next: { revalidate }` on `fetch`; don't rely on defaults.
- Named exports for components (no `export default function Page` beyond the framework's required
  route files). Use the `@/` alias for absolute imports.
- Secrets are server-only and never prefixed `NEXT_PUBLIC_`. Validate input on every server action.
